<p>This report of 1972 made a huge impact in The Netherlands and decided my choice of university engineering study in 1974 and in the years after I was busy constructing solar cells in the university laboratory, making computer models for wind turbines as well as storage of seasonal heat. Than Reagan came along, the cold war went into the over drive, funds for &#8216;alternative energy&#8217; dried up and most of these green lefties became yuppies, including me, making six figure salaries as independent professionals and travelled to five star hotels in tropical paradises around the globe. That period ended with 9/11. Worries about mass immigration, hand in hand with the rise and murder of Pim Fortuyn in the Netherlands, and soon after, I believe in 2004, I read a book about peakoil from Defeyess and next Heinberg. Was not really a shock, merely an awakening from the hibernate between 1984 and 2004. Currently I am no longer interested in 6 figure salaries and the accompaning workload, but instead I am glued to my computer screen and read everything about resourse depletion, peakoil, geopolitics, history.</p>
